---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---
<BaseLayout title="About Â· BRT Studio">
  <section>
    <span class="chip">About</span>
    <h1 class="hero-title">Design partners for teams navigating complexity.</h1>
    <p class="hero-lead">
      We are a small, senior-led studio that helps early-stage and scaling teams build products that feel cohesive,
      credible, and human. Our work spans product design, brand systems, and front-end collaboration.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="split">
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Principles</h2>
      <div class="timeline">
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <strong>Clarity over noise</strong>
          <span>Every screen should have a job and a reason.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <strong>Systems over heroics</strong>
          <span>We build reusable patterns that scale with teams.</span>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline-item">
          <strong>Momentum over perfection</strong>
          <span>Prototypes that lead to confident product decisions.</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="card">
      <h2>Capabilities</h2>
      <div class="tag-list">
        <span class="tag">Product Strategy</span>
        <span class="tag">UX Research</span>
        <span class="tag">Design Systems</span>
        <span class="tag">Visual Identity</span>
        <span class="tag">Front-end Collaboration</span>
        <span class="tag">User Testing</span>
      </div>
      <p style="margin-top: 18px;">
        We collaborate with engineering to keep design intent intact. Our outputs are lean, documented, and ready to
        ship.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="card">
    <h2>Team</h2>
    <p>
      BRT Studio is led by Ben Taylor and a rotating network of trusted designers, researchers, and engineers. We
      scale up as needed while keeping leadership hands-on.
    </p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
